data.enText: to wind into a series of circles; to make sth do this

data.chText: 那条蛇盘绕起来准备攻击。
data.enText: The snake coiled up, ready to strike.
Mist coiled around the tops of the hills.
to coil a rope into a loop
Her hair was coiled on top of her head.
a series of circles formed by winding up a length of rope, wire, etc.
one circle of rope, wire, etc. in a series
Shake the rope and let the coils unwind.
a length of wire, wound into circles, that can carry electricity

ex.chText: 那个工人把一根金属丝弯成一个圆圈。
ex.enText: The worker bends a piece of wire into a ring.

ex.chText: 那个小男孩想知道铜为什么容易弯折。
ex.enText: That little boy wonders why copper bends easily.

synonyms.bx: 指通过外力的作用使某物弯曲。

ex.chText: 狮子拱起后背向鹿扑去。
ex.enText: The lion arched its back to jump on the deer.

ex.chText: 树在人行道上方形成了一个拱顶。
ex.enText: Two rows of trees arched over the sidewalk.

synonyms.bx: 指身体某部位拱起或某物朝某方向拱起。

ex.enText: The branches were bowed by the heavy snow.
The trees bowed in the wind.

ex.chText: 她向客人深深地鞠了一躬。
ex.enText: She bowed deeply to her guest.
He bowed his head in shame.

synonyms.bx: 指某物在外力的作用下发生弯曲；用于人时，常表示鞠躬或由于羞愧而低头。

ex.enText: The snake coiled around the tree.

synonyms.bx: 强调卷绕或盘绕成环形。

ex.enText: The road curved to the left.

synonyms.bx: 指某物沿曲线运动或呈曲线形。

tr: a structure consisting of something wound in a continuous series of loops
reactor consisting of a spiral of insulated wire that introduces inductance into a circuit
tubing that is wound in a spiral
a contraceptive device placed inside a woman's womb
a transformer that supplies high voltage to spark plugs in a gasoline engine
a round shape formed by a series of concentric circles (as formed by leaves or flower petals)
wind around something in coils or loops

example: This famous potter hand-builds all of her vessels

tr: to wind or move in a spiral course
example: the muscles and nerves of his fine drawn body were coiling for action
black smoke coiling up into the sky
the young people gyrated on the dance floor

value.def: A coil of rope or wire is a length of it that has been wound into a series of loops.

example.ex: Tod shook his head angrily and slung the coil of rope over his shoulder...
example.tran: 托德气愤地摇了摇头，然后把那卷绳子往肩上一搭。

example.ex: The steel arrives at the factory in coils.
example.tran: 钢材被成卷地运到工厂。

value.def: A coil is one loop in a series of loops.

example.ex: Pythons kill by tightening their coils so that their victim cannot breathe.
example.tran: 大蟒蛇紧紧盘绕猎物使之无法呼吸，从而杀死猎物。

value.def: A coil is a thick spiral of wire through which an electrical current passes.
In a vehicle, the coil is the part on a petrol engine that sends electricity to the spark plugs.
The coil is a contraceptive device used by women. It is fitted inside a woman's womb, usually for several months or years.
If you coil something, you wind it into a series of loops or into the shape of a ring. If it coils around something, it forms loops or a ring.

example.ex: He turned off the water and began to coil the hose...
example.tran: 他关掉水龙头，开始盘水管。

example.ex: Louisa was dancing, spinning by herself, her skirt flying out and coiling around her feet...
example.tran: 路易莎打着圈儿翩翩起舞，裙摆时而肆意飞扬，时而盘绕脚边。

example.ex: A huge rattlesnake lay coiled on the blanket.
example.tran: 一条巨大的响尾蛇盘绕在毯子上。

example.ex: Once we have the wire, we can coil it up into the shape of a spring...
example.tran: 一旦有了金属丝，我们就能把它卷成弹簧的形状。

example.ex: Her hair was coiled up on top of her head.
